EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to Medicaid; requiring the Director of the
Department of Health and Human Services to seek to
establish certain rates of reimbursement under Medicaid
for vagus nerve stimulation therapy devices, replacement
parts for such a device and the procedures necessary to
implant, repair or replace a part of such a device; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Department of Health and Human Services to
2 administer the Medicaid program. (NRS 422.270) This bill requires the Director of
3 the Department to submit to the United States Secretary of Health and Human
4 Services a request to amend Medicaid to provide rates of reimbursement greater
5 than or equal to 82 percent of the cost for: (1) a vagus nerve stimulation therapy
6 device; (2) any replacement part for such a device; and (3) the procedure necessary
7 to implant, repair or replace a part of such a device. This bill also clarifies that the
8 rates of reimbursement established for the cost of a vagus nerve stimulation therapy
9 device and any replacement part for such a device must be separate from and in
10 addition to the rates of reimbursement for medical care necessary for the
11 implantation or repair of such a device or the replacement of a part for the device.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
